---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="The Van Guide is an independent editorial resource for van conversion owners and shoppers."
>
  <section class="container-read py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="eyebrow mb-4">About</div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl leading-tight mb-6">About The Van Guide</h1>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        The Van Guide is a directory of van conversion builders and a reference for the insurance, registration, and certification questions that come with owning one.
      </p>
      <p>
        The builder directory covers shops across the US. You can filter by state, platform, price range, and services. The editorial side covers which insurance carriers write policies on converted vans, how retitling works state by state, and what certifications like RVIA actually mean. Everything cites its source.
      </p>

      <h2>How this site makes money</h2>
      <p>
        Three ways:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Paid owner's guide</strong> — a single reference covering insurance, registration, and the buying process.</li>
        <li><strong>Affiliate links</strong> — disclosed on every page where they appear.</li>
        <li><strong>Verified builder listings</strong> — builders can <a href="/builders/claim/">claim their profile</a> and pay for enhanced features like photos and a longer description. Verified status is labeled and does not affect search position.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Corrections</h2>
      <p>
        If something on this site is wrong, send the URL and what needs fixing to <a href="mailto:hello@thevanguide.com">hello@thevanguide.com</a>. Include a source if you have one.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
